<!-- Water Audit Section -->

<style>
  /* Metrics boxes for water efficiency measures */
  .metrics-container {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 12px;
    margin: 15px 0 25px 0;
  }

  .metric-box {
    padding: 12px 15px;
    border-radius: 4px;
    min-width: 160px;
    flex: 1;
  }

  .metric-label {
    font-size: 12px;
    font-weight: 500;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }

  .metric-value {
    font-size: 20px;
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  /* Box-specific colors */
  .cost-savings {
    background-color: #ebffee;
  }

  .cost-savings .metric-label {
    color: #006837;
  }

  .water-savings {
    background-color: #ebf9ff;
  }

  .water-savings .metric-label {
    color: #005994;
  }

  .payback-period {
    background-color: #f9ebff;
  }

  .payback-period .metric-label {
    color: #8130a7;
  }
</style>

<h2 id="water-audit-introduction">A. Introduction</h2>
<p>
  This Water Audit report presents the findings of a water audit conducted at {{project.property_address}}.
  The audit includes an analysis of the building's water usage, identification of water conservation measures,
  and recommendations for implementation.
</p>

<h2 id="water-audit-procedures">B. Water Audit Procedures</h2>
<p>
  The water audit was conducted using the following procedures:
</p>
<ol>
  <li>On-site facility survey of existing water-using fixtures, equipment, systems, and processes</li>
  <li>Interview with operations and maintenance personnel</li>
  <li>Analysis of water bills and usage patterns</li>
  <li>Identification of water conservation opportunities</li>
  <li>Development of water efficiency measures</li>
  <li>Financial analysis of proposed measures</li>
</ol>

<h2 id="wems-cost-savings-summary-table">C. WEMs Cost Savings Summary Table</h2>
<table>
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>Measure</th>
      <th class="text-right">Annual Savings (gal)</th>
      <th class="text-right">Cost Savings ($)</th>
      <th class="text-right">Implementation Cost ($)</th>
      <th class="text-right">Payback (years)</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    {{#each waterMeasures}}
    <tr>
      <td>{{title}}</td>
      <td class="text-right">{{formatNumber estimatedSavings.water}}</td>
      <td class="text-right">{{formatCurrency estimatedSavings.cost}}</td>
      <td class="text-right">{{formatCurrency implementationCost}}</td>
      <td class="text-right">{{formatNumber estimatedSavings.paybackPeriod 1}}</td>
    </tr>
    {{else}}
    <tr>
      <td colspan="5" class="text-center">No water efficiency measures available</td>
    </tr>
    {{/each}}
  </tbody>
</table>

<h2 id="existing-conditions-observations-water">D. Existing Conditions and Observations</h2>

<h3 id="domestic-indoor-water-use">1. Domestic Indoor Water Use</h3>
<p>
  {{#if domesticWaterUse}}{{domesticWaterUse}}{{else}}The building's domestic indoor water use includes restroom
  fixtures (toilets, urinals, faucets), kitchen sinks, and drinking fountains. Many of the fixtures are original to the
  building and do not meet current water efficiency standards. There are opportunities for water savings through fixture
  upgrades.{{/if}}
</p>

<h3 id="non-domestic-indoor-water-use">2. Non-Domestic Indoor Water Use (CT, HVAC)</h3>
<p>
  {{#if nonDomesticWaterUse}}{{nonDomesticWaterUse}}{{else}}The building's non-domestic indoor water use includes
  cooling towers and HVAC systems. The cooling tower does not have adequate controls for optimizing water use. There are
  opportunities for water savings through equipment upgrades and control system improvements.{{/if}}
</p>

<h3 id="outdoor-water-use">3. Outdoor Water Use (Irrigation & Landscaping)</h3>
<p>
  {{#if outdoorWaterUse}}{{outdoorWaterUse}}{{else}}The building's outdoor water use includes irrigation for
  landscaping. The irrigation system is manually controlled and does not have weather-based controls. There are
  opportunities for water savings through irrigation system upgrades and drought-tolerant landscaping.{{/if}}
</p>

<h3 id="industrial-process-water-use">4. Industrial Process Water use</h3>
<p>
  {{#if industrialWaterUse}}{{industrialWaterUse}}{{else}}The building does not have any industrial process water
  use.{{/if}}
</p>

<h2 id="water-efficiency-measures-recommended">E. Water Efficiency Measures Recommended</h2>

{{#each waterMeasures}}
<h3 id="wem-{{@index}}">WEM {{add @index 1}}: {{title}}</h3>
<p>
  <strong>Description:</strong> {{recommendation}}
</p>

<!-- Metrics boxes for key values -->
<div class="metrics-container">
  <div class="metric-box cost-savings">
    <div class="metric-label">Annual Cost Savings</div>
    <div class="metric-value">${{formatNumber estimatedSavings.cost 0}}</div>
  </div>

  <div class="metric-box water-savings">
    <div class="metric-label">Water Savings</div>
    <div class="metric-value">{{formatNumber estimatedSavings.water 0}} gal/year</div>
  </div>

  <div class="metric-box payback-period">
    <div class="metric-label">Payback Period</div>
    <div class="metric-value">{{formatNumber estimatedSavings.paybackPeriod 1}} years</div>
  </div>
</div>

{{else}}
<p>No water efficiency measures have been identified at this time.</p>
{{/each}}

<h2 id="wems-already-implemented">F. WEMs Already Implemented</h2>
<p>
  {{#if implementedWaterMeasures}}
  The following water efficiency measures have already been implemented:
<ul>
  {{#each implementedWaterMeasures}}
  <li>{{this}}</li>
  {{/each}}
</ul>
{{else}}
No water efficiency measures have been previously implemented.
{{/if}}
</p>

<h2 id="wems-to-consider">G. WEMs to Consider</h2>
{{#if waterMeasuresToConsider}}
{{#each waterMeasuresToConsider}}
<h3>{{this.title}}</h3>
<p>{{this.recommendation}}</p>
{{/each}}
{{else}}
<p>No additional water efficiency measures to consider at this time.</p>
{{/if}}

<h2 id="wems-requiring-further-investigation">H. WEMs Requiring Further Investigation</h2>
{{#if waterMeasuresForInvestigation}}
{{#each waterMeasuresForInvestigation}}
<h3>{{this.title}}</h3>
<p>{{this.recommendation}}</p>
{{/each}}
{{else}}
<p>No water efficiency measures requiring further investigation at this time.</p>
{{/if}}

<h2 id="non-efficiency-water-measures">I. Non-Efficiency Water Measure/s</h2>
{{#if nonEfficiencyWaterMeasures}}
{{#each nonEfficiencyWaterMeasures}}
<h3>{{this.title}}</h3>
<p>{{this.recommendation}}</p>
{{/each}}
{{else}}
<p>No non-efficiency water measures have been identified at this time.</p>
{{/if}}

<h2 id="water-use-analysis">J. Water Use Analysis</h2>

<h3 id="building-water-use-intensity">1. Building Water Use Intensity (WUI)</h3>
<p>
  The building's water use intensity is {{formatNumber waterUseIntensity 2}} gallons per square foot per year.
</p>

<h3 id="energy-star-water-scorecard">2. ENERGY STAR® Water Scorecard</h3>
<p>
  {{#if waterScorecard}}
  The building has a water score of {{waterScorecard.score}}. This places the building in the
  {{waterScorecard.percentile}} percentile compared to similar buildings nationwide.
  {{else}}
  ENERGY STAR water benchmarking has not been performed for this building.
  {{/if}}
</p>

<h3 id="water-usage-and-cost">3. Water Usage and Cost</h3>
<p>
  The building's annual water consumption is {{formatNumber totalUsage.waterUsage}} gallons, with an average monthly
  consumption of {{formatNumber monthlyAvgWater}} gallons.
</p>

<h3 id="water-balance-chart">4. Water Balance Chart</h3>
<p>
  The following chart shows the breakdown of water usage by end use:
</p>
<!-- Insert chart here -->

<h3 id="water-consumption-table">5. Water Consumption Table</h3>
<table>
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>Month</th>
      <th class="text-right">Usage (gallons)</th>
      <th class="text-right">Cost ($)</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    {{#each monthlyData.water}}
    <tr>
      <td>{{this.month}}</td>
      <td class="text-right">{{formatNumber this.usage}}</td>
      <td class="text-right">{{formatCurrency this.cost}}</td>
    </tr>
    {{/each}}
  </tbody>
</table>
